# Private Submodule Mount Point

This directory is intentionally empty in the public repo.

If you have access to the `servicenow-agent-army-private` repo, mount it here as a git submodule:

  git submodule add git@github.com:paulopierrondi/servicenow-agent-army-private.git private

Or clone independently and symlink:

  git clone git@github.com:paulopierrondi/servicenow-agent-army-private.git ~/code/sa-army-private
  ln -s ~/code/sa-army-private private

The `private/` path is in `.gitignore` so it never leaks into the public repo.

See `docs/private-submodule-setup.md` for the full pattern.
